Turn Dates from Character Strings to Numeric/ Create new column of months

nlp_fb$date <- as.Date(as.POSIXct(nlp_fb$date, 'GMT'))

nlp_fb$month <- month(as.POSIXlt(nlp_fb$date, format = "%Y-%m-%d"))

Function and command to expand contractions

fix.contractions <- function(doc) {
  # "won't" is a special case as it does not expand to "wo not"
  doc <- gsub("won't", "will not", doc)
  doc <- gsub("can't", "can not", doc)
  doc <- gsub("n't", " not", doc)
  doc <- gsub("'ll", " will", doc)
  doc <- gsub("'re", " are", doc)
  doc <- gsub("'ve", " have", doc)
  doc <- gsub("'m", " am", doc)
  doc <- gsub("'d", " would", doc)
  # 's could be 'is' or could be possessive: it has no expansion
  doc <- gsub("'s", "", doc)
  return(doc)
}

nlp_fb$message <- sapply(nlp_fb$message, fix.contractions)

Function and command to remove URLs

removeSpecialChars <- function(x) {
  x <- gsub("(f|ht)(tp)(s?)(://)(\\S*)", "", x)
  x <- gsub(" #\\S*", "", x)
  x <- gsub("@[a-z,A-Z]*", "", x)
  x <- gsub("[^[:alnum:][:space:]'-]", "", x)
  x <- gsub("[^\x01-\x7F]", "", x)
  x <- gsub("[[:digit:]]+", "", x)
  return(x)
}

nlp_fb$message <- sapply(nlp_fb$message, removeSpecialChars)

Lower case characters

nlp_fb$message <- sapply(nlp_fb$message, tolower)

Undesirable Words based on sample and previous research

undesirable_words <- c("texas", "department", "transportation","private message", "theres", "fe0f", "yeah", "alright", "wanna", "gonna", "whoa", "gotta")

Tokenize, remove stopwords, undesirable words, and words less than three characters long

fb_tidy <- nlp_fb %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, message) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  filter(!word %in% undesirable_words) %>%
  filter(nchar(word) > 3)
## Joining, by = "word"

Pairwise Comparisons and Correlations

pwc <- fb_tidy %>%
  filter(n() >= 20) %>%  
  pairwise_count(word, date, sort = TRUE) %>%
  filter(item1 %in% c("love", "safe", "limit", "dangerous")) %>%
  group_by(item1) %>%
  slice(seq_len(7)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(row = -row_number())

pwc %>%
  ggplot(aes(row, n, fill = item1)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~item1, scales = "free") +
  scale_x_continuous(  #This handles replacement of row
    breaks = pwc$row, #Notice need to reuse data frame
    labels = pwc$item2) +
  theme_nlp() + theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank()) +
  xlab(NULL) + ylab(NULL) +
  ggtitle("Pairwise Counts") +
  coord_flip()

fb_tidy %>%
  group_by(word) %>%
  filter(n() >= 20) %>%
  pairwise_cor(word, date, sort = TRUE) %>%
  filter(item1 %in% c("love", "safe", "limit", "dangerous")) %>%
  group_by(item1) %>%
  top_n(7) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(item2 = reorder(item2, correlation)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(item2, correlation, fill = item1)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~item1, scales = 'free') +
  theme_nlp() + theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank()) +
  xlab(NULL) + ylab(NULL) +
  ggtitle("Pairwise Correlation") +
  coord_flip()

Bigrams Analysis

Previous analysis isolated single words. Bigrams introduce two word combinations

Bigrams by Month

fb_bigrams <- nlp_fb %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, message, token = "ngrams", n = 2)

bigrams_separated <- fb_bigrams %>%
  separate(bigram, c("word1", "word2"), sep = " ")

bigrams_filtered <- bigrams_separated %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% undesirable_words) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% undesirable_words)

bigram_month <- bigrams_filtered %>%
  filter(word1 != word2) %>%
  filter(month != "NA") %>%
  unite(bigram, word1, word2, sep = " ") %>%
  inner_join(nlp_fb) %>%
  count(bigram, month, sort = TRUE) %>%
  group_by(month) %>%
  slice(seq_len(7)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(month, n) %>%
  mutate(row = row_number())
## Joining, by = c("date", "post_permalink", "type", "month")

Negation Analysis to inlcude two word phrases with “Not” “No” “Never” “without”

AFINN <- get_sentiments("afinn")

negation_words <- c("not", "no", "never", "without")

negation_bigrams <- bigrams_separated %>%
  filter(word1 %in% negation_words) %>%
  inner_join(AFINN, by = c(word2 = "word")) %>%
  count(word1, word2, score, sort = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(contribution = n * score) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs(contribution))) %>%
  group_by(word1) %>%
  slice(seq_len(20)) %>%
  arrange(word1,desc(contribution)) %>%
  ungroup()

bigram_graph <- negation_bigrams %>%
  graph_from_data_frame() #From `igraph`

set.seed(123)

a <- grid::arrow(type = "closed", length = unit(.15, "inches"))

ggraph(bigram_graph, layout = "fr") +
  geom_edge_link(alpha = .25) +
  geom_edge_density(aes(fill = score)) +
  geom_node_point(color = "purple1", size = 1) + 
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name),  repel = TRUE) +
  theme_void() + theme(legend.position = "none",
                       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +
  ggtitle("Negation Bigram Network")

negation_bigrams %>%
  mutate(contribution = n * score) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs(contribution))) %>%
  head(20) %>%
  mutate(word2 = reorder(word2, contribution)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(word2, n * score, fill = n * score > 0)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  xlab("Words preceded by not, no, without, or never") +
  ylab("Sentiment score * number of occurrences") +
  coord_flip()

Trigram Analysis

Cleaning and Tokenization

fb_trigrams <- nlp_fb %>%
  unnest_tokens(trigram, message, token = "ngrams", n = 3)

trigrams_separated <- fb_trigrams %>%
  separate(trigram, c("word1", "word2", "word3"), sep = " ")

trigrams_filtered <- trigrams_separated %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word3 %in% stop_words$word)

Trigrams by month

Trigrams are useful with longer texts, but tweets and Facebook messages don’t produce the best results. I’m including these just incase you’d like to use them in your final report.

trigram_month <- trigrams_filtered %>%
